RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 61. Claiming Purse 7700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWO ANGELS forced the pace issue as the widest of four abreast along the backstretch and around the bend, headed the front runner at upper stretch, and bested that rival in final sixteenth for the score. GENUINE DRAFT broke alertly, established the inside line and saved ground around the bend, led the field in concert at upper stretch, but was outdueled in final strides. MISS TYRO rushed from outset and gained first command, led the field into the turn while trekking three wide, rated close up and between rivals at upper stretch, but failed to sustain the bid in closing stages. OUTWORKTHEOKIEGIRL trailed from outset, passed tiring rival, and failed to menace. LYNN'S FOLLY was hustled along the backstretch, rated close up and two wide at the head of the turn, was shuffled back mid turn, and rapidly faded in the homestretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Lynn's Folly
ENTRY.COMMENT: two wide, shuffled back mid trun

ENTRY.NAME: Genuine Draft
ENTRY.OWNER: Flying B Ranch Cattle Company LLC and Bartmann Dayton

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 40. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20460. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Horses That Started For a Claiming Price of $7,500 Or Less In Their Last Three Starts Least Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAMENTABLE JARIN was unhurried through the opening bend, closed the gap on leaders along the backstretch, swung five wide through the closing turn, had command at upper stretch, and finished under a stiff drive to be inching away at the end. MS. MORENA showed reserve in the early going, steadily advanced on the front runners along the backstretch, trekked three wide around the final turn, and finished with strong strides to secure the place. DIAMOND GAL rushed from the break and established a ground saving stance, maintained that line into the final turn, was in tight nearing the eighth pole, and rallied mildly to earn the show. COMPUTER VIRUS flashed early foot and led the field through the opening half while saving ground, was headed midway through the final bend, and failed to sustain the bid in final furlong. YOUNEEDTOCALMDOWN came up empty after pressing the pace from a four wide pose.

ENTRY.NAME: Lamentable Jarin
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, closed gap along backstretch, five wide upper,driving

ENTRY.NAME: Computer Virus
ENTRY.COMMENT: early foot, inside, failed to sustain bid

ENTRY.NAME: Diamond Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, in tight eighth pole, mild gain for show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Purse 19250. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of $30,000 At A Mile Or Over In 2022 - 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LACEY BOSS gained first command, saved ground, and never relished command for a wire to wire score. FIGHTINGTEMPTATION trekked the two path, led the second flight throughout, but was no match for wire to wire winner. J LOVE trailed the field from outset and passed a tiring foe in late going. ROSE OF EKITA settled in behind the pacesetter and gave chase from a three path pose before tiring in final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 49. Maiden Claiming Purse 6600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY GOLDEN PRIZE shared early command as the outer rival of three abreast, gained command along the backstretch, tucked to save ground through the closing bend, and just held off the rallying rival in late strides to procure the victory. BROOKE'S ALL IN settled into mid pack and savid ground in early stages before rallying strongly two wide at upper stretch to be nosed out and just miss the score. BRYANS SONG gave chase from a trailing stance through the opening half, rated three wide at upper stretch and earned the show with a late gain. NITRO NINA pressed the early pace as the widest rival in the early stages, rated two deep and within striking distance at upper stretch, but failed to produce a rally in closing strides. GOTOTHEWINDOW flashed early foot, led the field at first call, and steadily faded thereafter.

ENTRY.NAME: My Golden Prize
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide, inside upper, just held

ENTRY.NAME: Nitro Nina
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide early, two path upper, no late kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 4950. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE DECEMBER 15, 2022. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXCITING stalked the pacesetter from a three wide pose around the opening bend, circled foes near the quarter pole, led the field at upper streth, and finished under a stiff drive for the score. HOODOO BROWN was unhurried through the opening half while trekking an inside line, angled out at upper stretch, and was gaining on leaders at finish. LIMBO'S PROMISE broke alertly, shared command through the opening half while saving ground, but couldnt match strides with eventual winner in final sixteenth. RONALD DALE showed reserve and trailed the field through the opening half before closing with a rush to improve placing. REMEMBER ME TONY came up empty after pressing the early pace from a two path stance and swinging four deep at upper stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Remember Me Tony
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed two path, swung four path upper, empty

ENTRY.NAME: Hoodoo Brown
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, angled out upper, gaining at finish

ENTRY.NAME: Exciting
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked three wide, circled foes near quarter pole, driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 81. Allowance Purse 17600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OKLAHOMA STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILBERT gained first command, trekked the inside, and never relished for a wire to wire score. NEEDABETTERJOCK settled in behind the pacesetter, travelled the two path as the lone rival in second flight, but couldnt catch the leader in the end. MONET'S DEVIL saved ground to no avail. MAJOR GRIFFIN trekked the three path, gave chase from a back rated stance, and failed to threaten the leader. LITTLE SOLDIER BOY trailed from outset and was no menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Monet's Devil
ENTRY.OWNER: Flying B Ranch Cattle Company LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 86. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 6600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEET BAKER shook clear in final furlong after disputing the pace as the inner rival through the opening half. HE'S MUNNIE rushed form outset, set the pace in tandem as the outer rival of two abreast, but failed to match strides with that rival in final furlong. LARCH gave chase to pacesetting duo from a two path pose and as no threat to that top pair. BROTHER AARON was unhurried and established an inside stance, savedground throughout and was no factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Larch
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased two path, not near top pair

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 55. Claiming Purse 7150. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SARA'S SAPPHIRE established an inside pose shortly after the start, set the pace in tandem through the opening half, was headed near the eighth pole, latched into a stretch duel and showed courage in final sixteenth for the score. MO ARETHA staked the pacesetting trio around the first bend, gained command near the eighth pole, locked into a stretch duel, but was outdueled in losing strides. SCRAPPY PATCH showed reserve and rated three wide in a back rated flight through the opening half before closing fast and improving placing in the late going. FREYAS CATZ was unhurried and settled into the back rated flight between rivals, closed the gap on leaders along the backstretch, and was gaining on leaders at finish. MUSTANGMAGNA flashed early foot and rated between rivals around the first turn and along the backstretch before tiring in the crucial portion of contest. JOSIES SCORE settled into the back rated flight through the opening half, trekked the inside line and was no threat. SHE'S A PLAYER was hurried from outset and pressed the pace as the outer rival of three abreast through the opening half before retreating rapidly in the closing stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Josies Score
ENTRY.OWNER: Doyen Larry and Daniels Dwight L

ENTRY.NAME: Sara's Sapphire
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, headed eighth pole, fought back

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Donny & Angie Burton, Samuel Goodwin & Blanton & Perry LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 9 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 7920. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MEGA BOND rallied along the rail for the score after looming on the heels of the pacesetters through the opening half. SHIPMAN'S SONG rushed from outset, set the pace while trekking the two path, led the field into the homestretch, but couldnt fend off the rallying rival in closing strides. WHIP pressed the early pace as the widest rival of all through the opening turn, rated close up at upper stretch, but was outfinished by top pair in final sixteenth. OUR CORNERSTONE settled into mid pack, travelled wide early, and was best of rest but could not catch top trio in the end. CATALE STORM gave chase from a three path stance and finished evenly. CHARING CROSS was unhurried and trailed the field through the opening call before improving placing with strong late interest. HUNTER'S LEGACY lost ground to front runners with a wide journey. OKIE UNION faded rapidly in the latter portion of contest after flashing early speed and disputing the pace from a three path pose.

ENTRY.NAME: Mega Bond
ENTRY.OWNER: Higgins William H and Davidson M Brent

ENTRY.NAME: Shipman's Song
ENTRY.COMMENT: two path pace, caught in late strides

ENTRY.NAME: Our Cornerstone
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled mid pack, wide early, couldnt catch top trio
